<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-06-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-06-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-06-03"><hi rend="italic">June 3,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 671.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your telegram of the 28th
                            ultimo reading as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Colonial office has received following message from governor
                                    Sierra Leone: “Regret to report Reverend and Mrs. McGrew
                                    murdered Paina (Taima?) about 8th May.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>